          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Israel closes diplomatic doors</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-17-2.jpg" alt="Israel closes diplomatic doors" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Israel has <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20241216-friedrich-merz-german-conservative-gunning-to-become-chancellor" target="_blank">announced</a> the closure of its embassy in Dublin, citing what it calls Ireland’s “extreme anti-Israeli policies.” The decision follows Ireland’s recognition of a Palestinian state and its support for an International Court of Justice (ICJ) case accusing Israel of genocide in Gaza. Israeli Foreign Minister Gideon Sa’ar accused Ireland of antisemitic rhetoric. Ireland expressed regret over the closure of the embassy. Prime Minister Simon Harris rejects claims of anti-Israel sentiment, emphasizing Ireland’s commitment to peace, human rights, and international law.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Ireland has been highly <a href="https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/ireland-condemns-hamas-attack-stresses-need-for-moderate-voices/" target="_blank">critical</a> of Israel’s response to Hamas attacks on October 7. In November, Irish authorities declared they would <a href="https://www.cnbctv18.com/world/ireland-prepared-to-arrest-netanyahu-following-icc-warrant-says-pm-19513308.htm" target="_blank">detain</a> Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu if he visited Ireland under an ICC arrest warrant. The diplomatic rift shows growing tensions over international perspectives on the Israel-Palestine conflict. Ireland has historically felt a <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/03/29/middleeast/why-ireland-is-the-most-pro-palestinian-nation-in-europe-mime-intl/index.html" target="_blank">parallel</a> between itself and Palestine in its previous struggle with the British.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
