          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Twist in the tale</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Planned peace talks between Congo and Rwanda to address the ongoing conflict in eastern Congo were unexpectedly <a href="https://apnews.com/article/congo-rwanda-talks-angola-canceled-0177dc34c1b18b8b43599b3e9da54316" target="_blank">canceled</a>. Congo’s President Felix Tshisekedi and Rwanda’s President Paul Kagame were scheduled to meet in Angola, which has been mediating the negotiations. However, Congo’s presidency reported that Rwanda refused to attend, making the talks conditional on Congo’s direct dialogue with the M23 rebel group, which was a condition Congo rejected.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Rwanda later issued a statement saying the summit was postponed due to a lack of consensus over direct talks with M23. <a href="https://theconversation.com/m23-four-things-you-should-know-about-the-rebel-groups-campaign-in-rwanda-drc-conflict-195020" target="_blank">The M23 group</a>, allegedly backed by Rwanda, is one of the armed groups operating in mineral-rich eastern Congo. This region of Congo has seen decades of violence, leading to the <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/news/congo-ap-rwanda-united-states-felix-tshisekedi-b2664489.html" target="_blank">displacement</a> of over 7 million people.</p>
        </mj-text>
