          Niger’s Defense Ministry <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/africa/20241215-niger-defence-ministry-says-39-killed-in-horrific-attacks-near-burkina-faso-border" target="_blank">reported</a> that 39 civilians, including children, were killed in two attacks in the Tera region near the <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Burkina+Faso/@12.5880281,-4.5518253,6.75z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0xe2dca26d5a6709b:0x27930aed46836dab!8m2!3d12.238333!4d-1.561593!16zL20vMDE2OTk?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI0MTIxMS4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D" target="_blank">Burkina Faso</a> border between December 12 and 14. The attacks targeted the villages of Libiri and Kokorou and were blamed on jihadist groups linked to the Islamic State group and Al-Qaeda, who are active in the area. The region, part of the troubled borderlands with Burkina Faso and Mali, has seen a surge in violence, with recent attacks killing dozens of civilians and soldiers.</p>
